The Natalia Household Electricity Use

ETC1010

2018-09-05

Across days

Typically more energy use over the weekends, and Monday/Wednesday during the week.

Across hours, by work day vs holiday

There is more of a work day pattern of use on work days, with small amount of energy peak in the morning and much more so in the evenings. You tend to burn the midnight oil! On holidays it is more consistent use throughout the day, peaking in the evening around 8pm.

On the calendar

The weekend vs week day pattern is visible, and the evening peak usage most days. Looks like you were travelling in December, April and June. Some air conditioning use in November and January, and heating in June and July.
